Everton’s Dominic Calvert-Lewin, Heung-Min Son of Tottenham Hotspur and Liverpool winger Mohammed Salah are joint-top of the scoring chart with 11 goals apiece after Game Week 13 fixtures. Son and Salah both scored in the 1-1 draw of their match at Anfield, to catch up with Calvert-Lewin who failed to net in the Toffees’ 2-0 win at Leicester City. Patrick Bamford (Leeds United) added one more goal to his tally against Newcastle. On Thurday, Marcus Rashford also bagged a brace, as Manchester United came from behind to see off Sheffield United 3-2 at Bramall Lane. Premier League top scorers: 11 goals: Dominic Calvert-Lewin (Everton), Heung-Min Son (Tottenham), Mohammed Salah (Liverpool) 10 goals: Jamie Vardy (Leicester City) 9 goals: Harry Kane (Tottenham Hotspur), Patrick Bamford (Leeds) 7 goals: Callum Wilson (Newcastle), Wilfried Zaha (Crystal Palace), Bruno Fernandes (Manchester United) 6 goals: Ollie Watkins (Aston Villa), Danny Ings (Southampton) 5 goals: Jack Grealish (Aston Villa), Diogo Jota (Liverpool), Marcus Rashford (Manchester United)